DOCKER 101
-----------
docker run -d -p 80:80 docker/getting-started
    -d = run the container in the background (DETATCHED mode)
    -p 80:80 = map host_port:container_port (80:80)
    docker/getting-started = the image to use

can combine single character flags
    -d -p 80:80 --> -dp 80:80

CONTAINER: a process on your machine that has been isoated
    leverages kerneal namespaces and cgroups (old magic linux features)

CONTAINER IMAGE: provides the custom or isolated filesystem

Namespaces: What you can see, create with syscalls 
Change Root (Chroot):
Control Group: can prevent never ending loop

see BUILDING THE APPS CONTAINER IMAGE
see UPDATING THE APP